  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nBy running the `geth version` command:\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.9.25-stable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.19.7\r\nOperating System: linux (actually running on an OpenWrt image, inside QEMU x86_64 with kvm)\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=\r\n\r\nI am running an Ethereum private network with the clique PoA consensus algorithm, with multiple nodes as signers, and others as clients.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThis code exists within a very simple smart contract:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    int public count;\r\n\r\n    // Function to get the current count\r\n    function get() public view returns (int) {\r\n        return count;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // Function to increment count by 1\r\n    function inc() public {\r\n        count += 1;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // Function to decrement count by 1\r\n    function dec() public {\r\n        // This function will fail if count = 0\r\n        count -= 1;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, any call to this smart contract, more specifically to the `get()` function, always returns the value `-7.2143235047287905055446557179996963579510840293502015264854422142075635965924e+76` for the `count` variable.\r\n\r\nSimilar smart contracts, for example, with unsigned `uintXXX` variables would give me `4.3648854190028290368124427828690944273759144372138548774602369232303076466716e+76`.\r\n\r\nThere is something fundamentally wrong (probably with the whole system, maybe some system level dependency missing?) that I cannot uncover the cause.\r\nThe rest of the network operations work just fine, the blockchain is up and running, generating blocks and accepting usual transactions.",
